    "src/unit-tests/**/*.ts"
  ]
}
```

The base **`tsconfig.json`** uses strict mode with `strict: true`, but test config relaxes certain constraints for test files (no implicit any, null checks, etc.). Path aliases map `@modules/*`, `@utils/*`, `@constants/*`, etc. to their respective source directories.

---

### 3. Coverage Thresholds

**Global minimum: 95%** across all metrics (branches, functions, lines, statements)

- Unit tests exclude `/modules/db/` from coverage
- E2E tests exclude specific services and modules (bigquery, cli, load-test, newrelic, algolia, mms)
- E2E coverage collected only from `*.(controller|service).ts` files
- Coverage is enforced by Jest and will fail CI if thresholds are not met

