## Before Creating Any File

**ALWAYS inspect existing similar files first:**

```bash
# Services
ls src/modules/*/
# Controllers
ls src/modules/*/
# Utils
ls src/utils/
# DTOs
ls src/dto/
```

Read 2-3 similar files to understand exact patterns before writing anything.

## Import Aliases

```typescript
@config/*        → src/configs/*
@constants/*     → src/constants/*
@modules/*       → src/modules/*
@utils/*         → src/utils/*
@middlewares/*   → src/middlewares/*
@services/*      → src/services/*
@interfaces/*    → src/interfaces/*
@decorators/*    → src/decorators/*
@dto/*           → src/dto/*
@guards/*        → src/guards/*
@interceptors/*  → src/interceptors/*
```

## Creating Components

### Service

```typescript
import { Injectable, Logger } from '@nestjs/common';

import { EnvConfigService } from '@modules/env-config/env-config.service';
import { MY_VAR } from '@constants/env-variables.constant';

@Injectable()
export class MyService {
  private readonly logger = new Logger(MyService.name);

  constructor(private readonly configService: EnvConfigService) {}

  doSomething({ param }: { param: string }): string {
    this.logger.log(`Processing ${param}`);
    return param;
  }
}
```

### Controller

```typescript
import { Controller, Get, HttpStatus } from '@nestjs/common';
import { ApiOperation, ApiResponse, ApiTags } from '@nestjs/swagger';

import { MyService } from '@modules/my/my.service';

@ApiTags('My Module')
@Controller('my-endpoint')
export class MyController {
  constructor(private readonly myService: MyService) {}

  @Get()
  @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Get data' })
  @ApiResponse({ status: HttpStatus.OK, description: 'Success' })
  getData(): string {
    return this.myService.doSomething({ param: 'value' });
  }
}
```

### Module

```typescript
import { Module } from '@nestjs/common';

import { MyController } from '@modules/my/my.controller';
import { MyService } from '@modules/my/my.service';

@Module({
  controllers: [MyController],
  providers: [MyService],
  exports: [MyService],
})
export class MyModule {}
```

### Guard

```typescript
import { CanActivate, ExecutionContext, Injectable, UnauthorizedException } from '@nestjs/common';
import { Observable } from 'rxjs';

@Injectable()
export class MyGuard implements CanActivate {
  canActivate(
    context: ExecutionContext,
  ): boolean | Promise<boolean> | Observable<boolean> {
    const request = context.switchToHttp().getRequest();

    if (!request.headers['authorization']) {
      throw new UnauthorizedException('Missing authorization header');
    }

    return true;
  }
}
```

### DTO

```typescript
import { IsNotEmpty, IsOptional, IsString } from 'class-validator';
import { ApiProperty, ApiPropertyOptional } from '@nestjs/swagger';

export class CreateDto {
  @ApiProperty({ description: 'Name' })
  @IsString()
  @IsNotEmpty()
  name: string;

  @ApiPropertyOptional()
  @IsString()
  @IsOptional()
  description?: string;
}
```

## Environment Variables

Adding a new env var requires 5 steps — see `backend/CLAUDE.md` for full process:
1. Add to `.env`, `.env.test`, `.env.example`, `.env.test.example`
2. Add constant in `src/constants/env-variables.constant.ts`
3. Add validation in `src/configs/env-validations.config.ts`
4. Add to `src/utils/get-env-file.util.ts`
5. Add test in `test/env-config.module.e2e-spec.ts`

## Error Handling

```typescript
import { HttpException, HttpStatus } from '@nestjs/common';

getData({ id }: { id: string }): Data {
  const data = this.findById({ id });
  if (!data) {
    throw new HttpException('Not found', HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND);
  }
  return data;
}
```

## File Organization

```
src/modules/{feature}/
├── {feature}.module.ts
├── {feature}.controller.ts
└── {feature}.service.ts

src/dto/{feature}/
├── create-{feature}.dto.ts
└── response-{feature}.dto.ts

src/unit-tests/
└── {feature}.service.unit-spec.ts

test/
└── {feature}.e2e-spec.ts
```

## After Writing Code

1. Run **code-quality-skill**: `npm run code-quality-check` — must pass clean
2. Run **test-skill**: write tests, achieve ≥95% coverage

## Success Checklist

- ✅ Inspected existing similar files first
- ✅ NO COMMENTS in code
- ✅ Used `@aliases` (no relative imports)
- ✅ Explicit return types on all functions
- ✅ Single object destructuring params
- ✅ Logger from `@nestjs/common`
- ✅ Swagger decorators on controller methods
- ✅ DTOs with class-validator decorators
- ✅ code-quality-check passes
- ✅ Tests written, 95% coverage

